Date:  0/0/1869
Source:  TrNZI
Author:
Vol / Page:  1/III/41
Edition:
Quote:  All were alike firmly believed to be remembrances of what they had seen in the reinga, or unseen world (or place of the departed,) whither the spirit (Wairua) was supposed to have been during the sleep of the body. <i>Ibid.</i> I/III/42  ... this haunting spirit, or phantom,  (Kehua,) which haunted its former place of residence, when in the body, ... differed widely from the sensible intellectual spirit (Wairua), which had departed to the reinga and which was not feared.
Notes:  (Colenso Maori races)

